						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up near the Sōmēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Sādhāraṇa, Tadige, Friday.</hi> The details of the date cannot be verified.</p>						

						<p>The inscription records the death of a certain Maṇḍalika of <hi rend="bold">Uddhare,</hi> in a fight at the fort, during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kāvadēva.</hi> This latter person might have been the same as Kāmadēva of the Kadaṁba family, who was a feudatory of Sōmēs11vara IV, the Western Chālukya king. In characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
